						<p>West wall of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Vīra-Nārāyaṇadēva: No date: 12th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is also damaged and the date portion is lost. It appears to record a gift of money for burning two <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamp in the temple of Tiruv-Anantīśvaramuḍaiyār in Kaṇṇāḍipputtūr, by a certain Ulaguḍaimukkōkkiḻāṉaḍi, for his own merit.</p>						

